ATLAS=0.6.99
#ATLAS_RAILS_MASTER_KEY=123123
# Cantaloupe as reachable from INSIDE the web container, for server-side
# IIIF info.json reads (manifest dimensions). Browsers use the public
# iiif_host; leave unset when the two are the same. In compose:
#CERBERUS_IIIF_INTERNAL_HOST=http://iiif:8182

# Dual-JP2 gated-derivative model. MasterJp2 writes a capped display JP2 to
# the open root and a full-resolution JP2 to the gated root; thumbnails serve
# openly, while S/M/L downloads + deep-zoom serve only from the gated host
# behind its authorization delegate. Leave the roots unset to collapse both
# onto today's derivatives dir (single-Cantaloupe dev); leave the gated host
# unset to fall back to the public iiif_host. iiif_signing_secret is the HMAC
# secret shared with the gated host's delegate (signed download URLs + zoom
# grant cookie) — required in production, may be unset in single-host dev.
#CERBERUS_OPEN_DERIVATIVES_ROOT=/home/cerberus/images/open
#CERBERUS_GATED_DERIVATIVES_ROOT=/home/cerberus/images/gated
#CERBERUS_GATED_IIIF_HOST=http://iiif-gated:8182
#CERBERUS_IIIF_SIGNING_SECRET=change-me-shared-with-cantaloupe-delegate
